data.custom-station-types#Custom Station Type:
If you create additional station types in stationTypes.lua, you'll need to create corresponding items for each one.For example, if you add a cooking station type:
["cooking"] = {
    placeItem = 'cooking_station',
    -- ... rest of config
}
You'll need to add the cooking_station item:
['cooking_station'] = {
    label = 'Cooking Station',
    consume = 0,
    weight = 150,
    stack = false,
    close = false,
    client = {
        export = "sleepless_crafting.placeCraftStation",
    }
},
cooking_station = {
    name = 'cooking_station',
    label = 'Cooking Station',
    weight = 150,
    type = 'item',
    image = 'cooking_station.png',
    unique = true,
    useable = true,
    shouldClose = true,
    description = 'A portable cooking station'
},

data.configuration#Configuration:
The stationLocations table contains an array of station definitions:
local stationLocations = {
    {
        id = "general_1",
        type = 'general',
        origin = vector3(200.5908, -925.1364, 29.6919),
        heading = 336.9814,
        upgrade = 1,
        groups = {
            ['police'] = 1,
        }
    },
    -- Add more static stations here
}
Modules.register('stationLocations', stationLocations)

data.groups-with-grade-requirements-table#Gro:
groups = {
    ['police'] = 2,      -- Police grade 2 or higher
    ['ambulance'] = 1,   -- Ambulance grade 1 or higher
}
If groups is not specified or is an empty table, the station is accessible to everyone.

